.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-TCFILTERS 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.10.2" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-tcfilters \- traffic shaping filters (tc filter) for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I tcfilters
file defines
.BR tc (8)
classifier filters that classify packets into traffic classes without relying
on packet marks.  shorewall-nft can apply the corresponding fwmark filter configuration
directly via
.BR "shorewall\-nft apply\-tc"
(preferred — uses pyroute2, no tc(8) binary required) or generate a
shell script with
.B tc filter add
commands via
.BR "shorewall\-nft generate\-tc"
(portable fallback).

For mark-based classification (the recommended approach) use
.I mangle
or
.I tcrules
instead.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/tcfilters
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
CLASS	yes	Target class (INTERFACE:CLASSID)
SOURCE	yes	Source address/CIDR (or - for any)
DEST	yes	Destination address/CIDR (or - for any)
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
DPORT	no	Destination port filter
SPORT	no	Source port filter
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Classify DNS traffic directly into the high-priority class:
.RS
.nf
#CLASS    SOURCE  DEST  PROTO  DPORT
eth0:1    -       -     udp    53
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-tcdevices (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-tcclasses (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-mangle (5)

